Remove the rosemary leaves from their stem, leaving one inch at the top. Chop the rosemary leaves and mix through the lamb. Add the apricots, courgettes and olive oil. Cover the mixture and leave to marinate in the fridge for at least 30 minutes.Place the lamb stock into a pan and bring to the boil. Pour the stock over the couscous. Cover with cling film and leave for five minutes. Add the red onion, parsley and raisins to the couscous. Mix thoroughly and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Skewer the lamb onto the rosemary stalk, alternating with cubes of courgette and apricots. Place the lamb onto a medium hot griddle pan. Griddle the lamb, turning occasionally until it is browned on all sides and cooked through.To serve, place the couscous mix onto a serving plate. Place the kebab skewer over the couscous. To finish, drizzle with olive oil.